🚀 Simple a Full-Stack user manager Application Deployment on Google Cloud VM

Over the past few days, I built and deployed a full-stack Todo application using:

🔹 React.js (Frontend)
🔹 Node.js + Express.js (Backend)
🔹 MongoDB (Database)
🔹 Nginx (Reverse Proxy & Static File Server)
🔹 PM2 (Node.js Process Manager)
🔹 Google Cloud Compute Engine VM

Architecture:

Users → Nginx → React Frontend / Node.js API → MongoDB

Key things I learned during this project:

✅ Building and deploying a React production build
✅ Running a Node.js API in production using PM2
✅ Configuring Nginx as a reverse proxy
✅ Routing API requests through Nginx to avoid CORS issues
✅ Managing environment variables for frontend and backend
✅ Deploying and maintaining applications on a Linux VM
✅ Using GitHub and SSH for deployment workflows

One of the most interesting lessons was understanding why Nginx sits in front of Node.js:

* It serves static files efficiently
* It acts as a reverse proxy
* It improves security
* It simplifies HTTPS configuration
* It provides a production-ready architecture

This project helped me understand not only how to build a full-stack application, but also how modern web applications are deployed and managed in production environments.

